        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-tjb-lavender-200/50">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-2xl text-tjb-lavender-500">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-1">Lifetime access</h3>
              <p class="text-tjb-gray leading-relaxed">Watch between appointments. Revisit when your plan changes. Review before a provider meeting. It's yours to keep.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-tjb-lavender-200/50">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-2xl text-tjb-lavender-500">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-1">Watch at your own pace</h3>
              <p class="text-tjb-gray leading-relaxed">Short lessons — pause anytime, resume where you left off. No all-day commitment required.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       HOW THIS IS DIFFERENT FROM A CHECKLIST
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 prose">
      <h2>How this course is different from a free checklist</h2>
      <p>A free checklist tells you <em>what to include</em>. This course explains <strong>why each preference matters</strong>.</p>
      <p>Most birth plan templates hand you a list of checkboxes and send you on your way. But checking "delayed cord clamping" doesn't help if you don't know what that means, when it might not be possible, or how to bring it up with your provider.</p>
      <p>This course walks through real scenarios — <a href="/birth-plan-for-induction/" class="text-tjb-rose-500 font-semibold hover:text-tjb-rose-600 border-b border-transparent hover:border-tjb-rose-500 transition-all">what if you're induced?</a> What do you say when your provider suggests something you didn't plan for? These are the conversations the checklist doesn't prepare you for.</p>
      <p>Taught by <a href="/about/" class="text-tjb-rose-500 font-semibold hover:text-tjb-rose-600 border-b border-transparent hover:border-tjb-rose-500 transition-all">Shelbi Kohler</a>, a certified birth doula who has sat in the delivery room with hundreds of families — not a generic content creator reading from a script.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       THIS IS FOR YOU IF
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-tjb-cream">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3 fade-up">This course is for you if</p>
      <div class="w-10 h-0.5 bg-tjb-rose-500 mb-8"></div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-tjb-rose-500 mt-1 text-lg">✓</span>
          <p class="text-tjb-charcoal leading-relaxed">You downloaded a birth plan and stared at a blank page</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-tjb-rose-500 mt-1 text-lg">✓</span>
          <p class="text-tjb-charcoal leading-relaxed">You want to understand your options, not just check boxes</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-tjb-rose-500 mt-1 text-lg">✓</span>
          <p class="text-tjb-charcoal leading-relaxed">You're worried about being pressured into decisions you didn't choose</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-tjb-rose-500 mt-1 text-lg">✓</span>
          <p class="text-tjb-charcoal leading-relaxed">You want guidance you can revisit — not a one-time phone call</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-tjb-rose-500 mt-1 text-lg">✓</span>
          <p class="text-tjb-charcoal leading-relaxed">You've had a birth before and want to make different choices this time</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       COURSE CURRICULUM
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Course curriculum</p>
      <div class="w-10 h-0.5 bg-tjb-rose-500 mb-8"></div>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-tjb-lavender-500 pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">01 — About me and my preferences</h3>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray leading-relaxed">How to fill in the "About Me" section so your care team sees you as a person, not a chart number. What to include in your flexibility statement. How to note trauma history, sensory needs, or religious preferences so they get read — not skipped.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-tjb-lavender-500 pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">02 — Labor and delivery</h3>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray leading-relaxed">The section that confuses most first-time parents. We walk through monitoring, IV, movement, environment, pain management, induction, and augmentation — what each choice actually looks like in the room, what your provider typically recommends and why, and how to say "I'd like to understand the reasoning" without feeling confrontational.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-tjb-lavender-500 pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">03 — Pain management preferences</h3>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray leading-relaxed">More than "epidural or unmedicated." We cover the full pain management ladder — from breathing techniques and position changes to IV meds and epidural placement — with honest context about timing, tradeoffs, and how to keep your options open at each stage.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-tjb-lavender-500 pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">04 — Post-delivery and newborn care</h3>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray leading-relaxed">Skin-to-skin, cord clamping, golden hour, feeding, Vitamin K, Hep B, eye ointment, circumcision, rooming-in, newborn screenings. These decisions happen fast after delivery. We make sure you know what each one is, what your hospital's default is, and how to state your preference clearly in advance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-tjb-rose-500 pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">05 — Advocacy and consent phrases</h3>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray leading-relaxed">The part most birth plans skip entirely — what to actually say when something unexpected comes up. "I need a minute to think," "What happens if we wait?," "Can you explain the reasoning?" These aren't confrontational. They're calm, clear, and effective. We practice them so they're ready when you need them.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-tjb-sage pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">06 — Plan B, Plan C, and flexibility language</h3>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray leading-relaxed">Birth is unpredictable. That doesn't mean you shouldn't plan — it means your plan needs language for change. We help you write backup preferences for common scenario shifts (induction, C-section, extended monitoring) so you still have a voice even when things don't go as expected. See our <a href="/birth-plan-for-induction/" class="text-tjb-rose-500 font-semibold hover:text-tjb-rose-600 border-b border-transparent hover:border-tjb-rose-500 transition-all">induction birth plan</a> and <a href="/c-section-birth-plan/" class="text-tjb-rose-500 font-semibold hover:text-tjb-rose-600 border-b border-transparent hover:border-tjb-rose-500 transition-all">C-section birth plan</a> pages for scenario-specific guidance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       PRICING
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-tjb-cream">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3 fade-up">Pricing</p>
      <div class="w-10 h-0.5 bg-tjb-rose-500 mb-8"></div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 shadow-sm border border-tjb-lavender-200/50">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-4">$47 one-time</h2>
        <p class="text-tjb-gray mb-6">No subscription. No upsell traps. Lifetime access to all modules.</p>
